value.title: Obama ethics chief blasts Hunter Biden's art scheme as 'absolutely appalling'
value.excerpt: Former President Obama's ethics chief on Wednesday ripped the Biden White House for brokering a deal last month so that Hunter Biden, and the American public at large, would never know who was buying his paintings.

value.title: Biden ally claims Trump greater 'threat' to US than al Qaeda
value.excerpt: A Democratic insider and vocal ally of President Biden claimed last week that former President Trump and his “Trumpist” supporters are a bigger threat to the United States than the Taliban and al Qaeda fighters.

value.title: With Biden poll numbers plunging, Democrats worry Afghan exit may impact next year's elections
value.excerpt: The rushed U.S. evacuation in Afghanistan appears to be a key contributing factor in the plunge in President Biden's approval rating in new polls. Some Democrats are worried the political fallout could impair their prospects in the 2022 midterms.

value.title: Pence slams Biden’s troop withdrawal as ‘foreign policy humiliation’
value.excerpt: In an interview on The Brian Kilmeade Show, Pence recalled Biden’s decision to fully withdraw by Sept. 11, saying that decision set the “disaster in motion.”

value.title: Sasse urges Biden to tell Taliban 'we're getting our people out however long it takes': 'Damn the deadline'
value.excerpt: In a blistering statement, Sen. Ben Sasse said Biden should be calling the shots, not the Taliban, who said there would be "no extensions" of the deadline set for withdrawal.

value.title: Kamala Harris' plane from Singapore delayed over possible 'Havana syndrome' incident
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris’ plane was delayed in Singapore on Tuesday for three hours after a possible case of the mysterious "Havana syndrome."

value.title: Kamala Harris calls Biden's Afghanistan decision 'courageous' as others in White House blame Trump
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris gave credit to President Biden for deciding to end the war in Afghanistan, even though members of the administration – including Biden himself – have blamed former President Trump for agreeing to withdraw U.S. troops.

value.title: Biden to be briefed on intelligence community COVID origin review as early as Tuesday
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to receive a briefing on the origin of COVID-19 from the intelligence community as early as Tuesday.

value.title: Trump calls on Florida judge to help reinstate his Youtube account
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Monday asked a Florida judge to issue a preliminary injunction in his case against YouTube that would compel the company to reinstate his access to the platform.

value.title: Harris rebukes China in major speech on Indo-Pacific
value.excerpt: U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a sharp rebuke to China for its incursions in the South China Sea, warning its actions there amount to “coercion” and “intimidation” and affirming that the U.S. will support its allies in the region against Beijing’s advances.

value.title: Thiessen: Biden handed terrorists a 'safe haven' to plan attacks worse than 9/11
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor Marc Thiessen told “America's Newsroom” that Biden has given radical Islamic terrorists, including Al-Qaeda, the tools they need to conduct attacks potentially deadlier than 9/11.

value.title: Meghan McCain compares Kamala Harris’ ‘craven’ uncontrollable laughing to Joaquin Phoenix’s ‘Joker’
value.excerpt: Former "View" co-host Meghan McCain scolded Vice President Kamala Harris Monday for laughing when asked about the ongoing crisis in Afghanistan, comparing the "craven" veep to Joaquin Phoenix’s mentally troubled character in the 2019 film "Joker.

value.title: Nevada Senate candidate Adam Laxalt says his Trump ties will energize base, give GOP majority in 2022
value.excerpt: Republicans see Nevada as their ticket to put the brakes on President Biden's agenda for the final two years of his term. And Senate candidate Adam Laxalt believes that his support for former President Trump will help put him over the top in the state Republicans have had trouble winning for years.

value.title: Gowdy: Biden claimed to be 'Moses leading us out of the wilderness' and the media fell for it. We knew better
value.excerpt: Sunday Night in America” host Trey Gowdy blamed President Biden for the “women and children killed in the streets” of Afghanistan during a passionate opening monologue Sunday night where he addressed the deteriorating situation as the Taliban continues to gain control in the region.

value.title: John Ratcliffe: Adversaries are going to use Biden's failure as propaganda
value.excerpt: Former Director of National Intelligence John Ratcliffe spoke with Trey Gowdy on international consequences following the Afghanistan crisis.

value.title: West Virginia AG sues Biden admin over border policy reversal tied to ‘devastating’ fentanyl flow
value.excerpt: West Virginia Attorney General Patrick Morrisey is suing the Biden administration over a key immigration policy reversal he says has fueled a "devastating" flow in the deadly drug fentanyl.

value.title: Republicans torch White House for claiming Biden never 'shies away' from questions
value.excerpt: GOP lawmakers are smashing Biden over White House communications director Kate Bedingfield’s Friday claim that the president does not turn away from questions.

value.title: Federal judge blocks Biden admin's ICE rules that narrowed illegal immigrant arrest priorities
value.excerpt: A federal judge on Thursday imposed a preliminary injunction on the Biden administration’s rules for ICE officers that narrowed the categories of illegal immigrants targeted for arrest and deportation.

value.title: Trump acting DNI Grenell: Taliban should hear 'very tough message,' slams Biden for 'ignoring the conditions'
value.excerpt: Former acting Director of National Intelligence Ric Grenell slammed President Biden for having "ignored the conditions" set by former President Donald Trump in his 2020 agreement with the Taliban.

value.excerpt: Biden announced a plan to offer COVID-19 vaccine booster shots beginning the week of September 20

value.title: Vivek Ramaswamy calls out Kamala Harris' silence on Afghan women: 'She's totally lost'
value.excerpt: Vivek Ramaswamy, author of Woke, Inc., called out Vice President Kamala Harris for her silence as some Afghan women face civil rights violations at the hands of the Taliban. Ramaswamy called it a ‘wasted opportunity’ for the vice president who could have positioned herself as a leader on women's rights.

value.title: CNN’s Jeffrey Toobin ripped over column arguing against prosecuting Trump

value.title: Pelosi, top House Dems won't budge in infrastructure tussle with moderates, tout Biden support for her 'rule'
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and her leadership team are mounting a pressure campaign on centrist Democrats to get them to support their party's budget resolution without a vote on the bipartisan infrastructure bill.

value.title: Vivek Ramaswamy blasts Twitter's 'staggering' hypocrisy on Taliban and Trump
value.excerpt: Biotech CEO and ‘Woke Inc.’ author Vivek Ramaswamy criticized Twitter on Tuesday for allowing the Taliban to utilize their social media platform while censoring others, including former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Biden's speech was 'disingenuous,' al Qaeda will return, former Reagan official says
value.excerpt: A former assistant defense secretary warned that al Qaeda “will again show its viper head” and said President Biden was “disingenuous” and during his address Monday.

value.title: Biden approves Florida emergency declaration due to Tropical Storm Fred
value.excerpt: Biden ordered federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local response efforts -- because of emergency conditions resulting from the storm, according to a statement from the White House.

value.title: Trump calls on Biden to 'resign in disgrace' over crisis in Afghanistan
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump Sunday called on President Biden to “resign in disgrace” over his handling of the Afghanistan withdrawal and other issues.

value.title: Todd wondered if the messy Afghan withdrawal will 'weaken Trump's hold' of the GOP over time
value.excerpt: NBC anchor Chuck Todd spoke with certainty that the turmoil that has erupted during President Biden's military withdrawal in Afghanistan would have also occurred under President Trump.
